'''Marten Elco de Roon''' (born 29 March 1991) is a Dutch professional [[footballer]] who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] for {{Italian football updater|Atalanta}} club [[Atalanta BC|Atalanta]] and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands national team]].

After representing various Dutch youth teams, he started his career at [[Sparta Rotterdam]], and also played for [[SC Heerenveen]] in his home country before moving to Italian club [[Atalanta BC|Atalanta]] in 2015. He also played for English club [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] before rejoining Atalanta in 2017. He became Atalanta's all-time appearance maker in 2026.

De Roon is a Dutch international, having played for the Netherlands at the U19 level before making his senior debut in 2016. He was named in the Dutch squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2020]], [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] and [[2026 FIFA World Cup|2026 World Cup]].

==Early life==
De Roon was born in [[Zwijndrecht, Netherlands|Zwijndrecht]]<ref name=nrc-a1595160>{{cite web|last1=Butter |first1=Jan Cees |url=https://www.nrc.nl/nieuws/2018/03/09/een-harde-werker-gemaakt-voor-atalanta-bergamo-a1595160|title=Een harde werker, gemaakt voor Atalanta Bergamo|language=nl|website=nrc.nl|publisher=NRC|date=9 March 2018|access-date=16 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ad.nl/buitenlands-voetbal/centrocampista-de-roon-voetbalt-als-een-typische-italiaan~a66d9193/|title='Centrocampista' De Roon voetbalt als een typische Italiaan|language=nl|website=ad.nl|publisher=DPG Media|date=14 April 2019|access-date=16 March 2020}}</ref> and raised in [[Hendrik-Ido-Ambacht]],<ref name=omarm>{{cite web|url=https://www.volkskrant.nl/nieuws-achtergrond/omarm-de-spanning-en-win~b98c47478/|title=Omarm de spanning - en win!|language=nl|website=volkskrant.nl|publisher=DPG Media|date=22 March 2014|access-date=16 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ad.nl/buitenlands-voetbal/de-roon-na-verloren-bekerfinale-dagje-treuren-en-dan-vol-voor-champions-league~a4ad9fff/|title=De Roon na verloren bekerfinale: 'Dagje treuren en dan vol voor Champions League'|language=nl|website=ad.nl|publisher=DPG Media|date=16 May 2019|access-date=16 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ad.nl/buitenlands-voetbal/de-roon-keert-na-jaar-middlesbrough-terug-bij-atalanta~a3f002f5/|title=De Roon keert na jaar Middlesbrough terug bij Atalanta|language=nl|website=ad.nl|publisher=DPG Media|date=10 August 2017|access-date=16 March 2020}}</ref> where he played in youth teams of [[ASWH]].<ref name=nrc-a1595160/><ref name=omarm/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/nl/news/662/specials/2017/01/16/31586332/column-het-loonstrookje-van-de-roon|title=COLUMN - Het loonstrookje van De Roon|language=nl|website=goal.com|publisher=Goal|date=16 January 2017|access-date=16 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.weekbladdebrug.nl/nieuws/sport/ex-aswh-jeugdspeler-marten-roon-maakt-debuut-oranje/|title=Ex-ASWH jeugdspeler Marten de Roon maakt debuut in Oranje|language=nl|website=weekbladdebrug.nl|publisher=Xebius Media Groep|date=14 November 2016|access-date=16 March 2020|archive-date=19 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210519040912/https://www.weekbladdebrug.nl/nieuws/sport/ex-aswh-jeugdspeler-marten-roon-maakt-debuut-oranje/|url-status=dead}}</ref> From ASWH, he continued to youth teams of [[Feyenoord]] and [[Sparta Rotterdam]].

==Club career==
===Sparta Rotterdam===
De Roon made his [[Eredivisie]] debut for [[Sparta Rotterdam]] on 27 March 2010, starting in the match against [[FC Twente|Twente]] at [[De Grolsch Veste]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2010/03/27/netherlands/eredivisie/stichting-fc-twente-65/sparta-rotterdam-bv/781831/ |title=Twente vs. Sparta Rotterdam |publisher=Soccerway |date=27 March 2010 |access-date=26 May 2010}}</ref> He made a total of three appearances in the Eredivisie for the [[2009–10 Eredivisie|2009–10 season]].

===Heerenveen===
In April 2012, Eredivisie club [[SC Heerenveen]] announced the signing of De Roon on a three-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sc-heerenveen.nl/nieuws/marten-de-roon-tot-zomer-2017-bij-sc-heerenveen/10|title=Marten de Roon tot zomer 2017 bij sc Heerenveen|date=28 February 2015|website=www.sc-heerenveen.nl|publisher=SC Heerenveen|language=nl|access-date=8 July 2016|archive-date=30 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180830142320/https://www.sc-heerenveen.nl/nieuws/marten-de-roon-tot-zomer-2017-bij-sc-heerenveen/10|url-status=dead}}</ref>

===Atalanta===
In July 2015, De Roon was signed by [[Serie A]] side [[Atalanta B.C.|Atalanta]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.atalanta.it/site/paginalive/comunicati-dal-club/Stagione-2015-2016/2015-07/11-10-Mercato-Atalanta-Marten-De-Roon.html|title=Mercato Atalanta, Marten De Roon all'Atalanta a titolo definitivo|date=11 July 2015|website=www.atalanta.it|publisher=Atalanta B.C.|language=it|access-date=8 July 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923185730/http://www.atalanta.it/site/paginalive/comunicati-dal-club/Stagione-2015-2016/2015-07/11-10-Mercato-Atalanta-Marten-De-Roon.html|archive-date=23 September 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>

===Middlesbrough===
On 4 July 2016, De Roon signed for newly-promoted [[Premier League]] side [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] for a reported [[Pound sterling|£]]12&nbsp;million transfer fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mfc.co.uk/news/article/2016/middlesbrough-fc-marten-de-roon-atalanta-3171874.aspx|title=Marten de Roon: Boro Move Is An Honour For Me|date=July 2016}}</ref> He scored his first goal for his new club – a 91st-minute equaliser – on 5 November 2016 in a 1–1 draw with [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] at the [[City of Manchester Stadium|Etihad Stadium]]. He went on to score a further 3 league goals for the club over the remainder of the season, including the only goal in a victory over [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] in the [[Tees–Wear derby]], however Middlesbrough were relegated on 8 May 2017.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39767793|title=Middlesbrough relegated|work=BBC Sport |date=May 2017}}</ref> On 18 July 2017, Middlesbrough confirmed that they paid £8.8&nbsp;million for De Roon, with Atalanta earning another £900,000 after the midfielder played 30 games for the club.<ref>{{cite web|title=MFC – Clarifying Transfer Facts|url=http://www.mfc.co.uk/news/mfc-clarifying-transfer-facts|website=mfc.co.uk|publisher=Middlesbrough F.C.|access-date=18 July 2017|date=18 July 2017}}</ref>

===Return to Atalanta===
On 10 August 2017, De Roon re-signed for Atalanta for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/10982622/middlesbrough-midfielder-marten-de-roon-joins-atalanta|title=Middlesbrough midfielder Marten De Roon joins Atalanta|date=10 August 2017|website=www.skysports.com|publisher=Sky Sports}}</ref> He once again cemented himself as a starter under [[Gian Piero Gasperini]], and helped Atalanta finish in a historic 3rd place in the [[2018–19 Serie A|2018–19]] season, earning them a spot in the [[2019–20 UEFA Champions League group stage]]. He also scored a volley against [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]] in the [[2018–19 Coppa Italia|Coppa Italia]] semi-finals in the 58th minute.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fotmob.com/news/88kjiizg08wr1s4nbwcyslnqi-fiorentina-3-atalanta-3:-muriel-sets-up-mouth-watering-second-leg|title=Fiorentina 3 Atalanta 3: Muriel sets up mouth-watering second leg|website=FotMob|date=27 February 2019 |access-date=12 December 2019}}</ref> Atalanta would win the tie 5–4, though lost in the [[2019 Coppa Italia Final|final]] against [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/11721055/lazio-2-0-atalanta-late-show-gives-simone-inzaghis-lazio-first-major-trophy-in-five-years|title=Lazio 2-0 Atalanta: Late show gives Simone Inzaghi's Lazio first major trophy in five years|website=Sky Sports|language=en|access-date=12 December 2019}}</ref> He made his Champions League debut on 18 September 2019 against [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/din-zagreb-vs-atalanta/420350|title=Champions League (Sky Sports)|website=SkySports|language=en|access-date=12 December 2019}}</ref>

In the 2023–24 season, he frequently captained his team and marked a milestone by playing his 250th Serie A match in a 3–0 away victory over [[Empoli F.C.|Empoli]], becoming the first foreign player to reach this achievement at the club.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/atalanta-midfielder-marten-de-roon-becomes-the-first-foreign-player-to-reach-250-serie-a-appearances-for-the-club-38481819 |title=Atalanta midfielder Marten de Roon becomes the first foreign player to reach 250 Serie A appearances for the club |publisher=OneFootball |date=31 October 2023 }}</ref> On 15 May 2024, he suffered a knee injury during the [[2024 Coppa Italia final|Coppa Italia final]] against [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]], which resulted in a 1–0 defeat. This injury also sidelined him for the [[2024 UEFA Europa League final|Europa League final]], where his team secured their first-ever title in the competition with a 3–0 win over [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/de/news/de-roon-confirms-hell-miss-europa-league-final-the-biggest-nightmare-39503875 |title=De Roon confirms he'll miss Europa League Final: 'The biggest nightmare' |publisher=OneFootball |date=17 May 2024 }}</ref> On 22 March 2026, De Roon made his 436th appearance for Atalanta in a 1-0 home win against [[Hellas Verona FC|Hellas Verona]], surpassing former captain [[Gianpaolo Bellini]] as the club's all-time record appearance maker.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.flashscore.com/news/soccer-serie-a-marten-de-roon-breaks-atalanta-record-with-436th-club-appearance/8lGzskbf/|title=Marten de Roon breaks Atalanta record with 436th club appearance|publisher=Flashscore|date=2026-03-22|access-date=2026-04-08}}</ref>

==International career==
De Roon has represented the [[Netherlands national under-19 football team|Netherlands under-19 national team]] in the qualification rounds for the [[2010 UEFA European Under-19 Football Championship]]. On 12 November 2009, he made his debut and scored his first goal for the U-19 ''Oranje'' in a qualification match against [[Malta national under-19 football team|Malta]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/under19/match/304707--netherlands-vs-malta/ |title=Under-19 2010 – Netherlands-Malta |publisher=[[UEFA]] |date=8 November 2009 |access-date=26 May 2010}}</ref> On 13 November 2016, De Roon made his debut for the [[Netherlands national football team|senior team]] in a [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2018 FIFA World Cup qualification]] against [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=De Roon viert debuut met yoghurt in plaats van bier|url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2142986-de-roon-viert-debuut-met-yoghurt-in-plaats-van-bier|publisher=[[Nederlandse Omroep Stichting]]|date=13 November 2016|access-date=18 June 2025|language=nl}}</ref>

He was later named in the first Dutch squad chosen by new national team manager [[Ronald Koeman]]. This was in March 2018 for the [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly matches]] against [[England national football team|England]] and [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/koeman-puts-trust-in-newcomers-as-dutch-prepare-to-play-england_sto6678015/story.shtml|title=Ronald Koeman puts trust in Dutch youth, Justin Kluivert given first call-up|website=Eurosport|publisher=TNT Sports International|date=16 March 2018|access-date=13 June 2021}}</ref>

On 26 May 2021, he was named in the Dutch squad for the postponed [[UEFA Euro 2020]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/nieuws/nederlands-elftal/79017/frank-de-boer-maakt-ek-selectie-bekend |title=Frank de Boer maakt EK-selectie bekend |trans-title=Frank de Boer announces European Championship squad |publisher=[[Royal Dutch Football Association]] |date=26 May 2021 |access-date=26 May 2021 |language=nl}}</ref> On 11 November 2022, he was called up for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/nieuws/nederlands-elftal/80525/van-gaal-maakt-26-koppige-wk-selectie-bekend |title=Van Gaal maakt 26-koppige WK-selectie bekend |trans-title=Van Gaal announces 26-man World Cup squad |publisher=[[Royal Dutch Football Association]] |date=11 November 2022 |access-date=12 November 2022 |language=nl}}</ref> Later on, he missed the [[UEFA Euro 2024]] due to a knee injury.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/de-roon-set-to-miss-euro-2024-after-coppa-italia-injury-picture-39549226 |title=De Roon set to miss Euro 2024 after Coppa Italia injury – picture |website=OneFootball |date=27 May 2024 }}</ref>

